        public void addRandomNodes​(int amount)
        Creates a certain amount of nodes with a random placement on the map. The method wil ensure the created nodes will have a certain edge from the border of the map and a certain distance from each other.
        Parameters:
        amount - number of nodes to create

      • getNewNodeForPath

        Node getNewNodeForPath​(javafx.scene.shape.Path path)
        Creates a new node to appear on a newly drawn edge and adjusts its position so that there is no collision with existing nodes or edges. Returns null if no such node can be found. The new node is allowed to overlap other parts of its own edge.

        non-colliding node if one exists, null otherwise

      • drawPath

        public void drawPath​(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent mouseDrag)
              throws PathForcedToEnd,
                     InvalidPath,
                     CollisionException
        This method draws the line the user is tracing with their mouse. The method performs sub calls to pathSelfCollides() and pathCollidesWithOtherEdges() to ensure the drawn line is not intersecting with itself or other lines. The current drawing is removed if it violates the rules.
        Parameters:
        mouseDrag - A mouse drag
        Throws:
        PathForcedToEnd
        InvalidPath
        CollisionException

      • checkIfMouseHasExceededCanvasFrame

        Throws:
        InvalidPath - If mouse has exceeded canvas frame

      • startOrEndPath

        private void startOrEndPath​(boolean mouseIsInsideANode)
                     throws PathForcedToEnd
        Checks if drawing has left the start node, and starts the path with its first path element if it has. Checks if drawing has reached an end node, and ends the path with the final path element if it has.
        Parameters:
        mouseIsInsideANode - : True if mouse is currently on a node
        Throws:
        PathForcedToEnd - if the mouse has hit an end node

      • atLeastOneRemainingLegalMove

        private boolean atLeastOneRemainingLegalMove​(boolean smartMode)
        Analyzes if there is at least one legal move left in the game by making draw edge simulations. Used to update the game flow.
        Parameters:
        smartMode - : True if the game is dynamic or drag-to-draw, false otherwise
        Returns:
        true if there is at least one legal move left in the game, false otherwise

      • thereIsALegalEdge

        private boolean thereIsALegalEdge​(boolean smartMode,
                                  Node node1,
                                  Node node2)
        Checks if there is a legal edge between the input nodes. Calls the draw methods and returns true if no exceptions are thrown.
        Parameters:
        smartMode - : True if the function is called when game is in smart mode, false otherwise
        node1 - : First mode
        node2 - : Second node
        Returns:
        true if there is a legal edge between the nodes, false otherwise
